I don't think that the information contained in an MR record is of any
use to the network at large. I think that is information for the local
mailer. For instance, what should a mailer do with an address like
postmaster@Berkeley.EDU? Should it ask around and find that it
magically transposes into "rwh" and then ask for an MB record to see
that it should send "rwh" to the machine "ernie.Berkeley.EDU" and then
... ad nauseum, or should it simply deposit the mail at Berkeley.EDU
and let the local mailer worry about it?

These records don't seem to have any utility ...

/jordan

